_json.gridTitle: When You're The Pastor, But They Won't Let You Lead - Ron Edmondson
_json.description: I was talking with a 25 year old pastor recently.  He is frustrated with his church.  He was brought to the church because they wanted him to help the church grown again, but they see him as too young to make decisions on his own.  They won’t take his suggestions.  They consistently undermine his attempts to lead.  They expect him to speak each week and visit the sick, but they won’t let him make any changes that he feels need to be made.
